author: Special to syracuse.com
title: Mike Mahaney, Mark Smith wins rescheduled race at Rolling Wheels Raceway
text:
By Dick O'Brien
Super DIRT Week 2015 officially ended Sunday night at Rolling Wheels Raceway Park with the running of the rescheduled Empire Super Sprint/DIRT 358 modified doubleheader.
The modified finale saw Mike Mahaney shoot off the pole, and the King Ferry pilot was a green-to-checker victor in the 35-lap main event. He pocketed $4,000.
Ryan Arbuthnot was a distant second, with Matt Delorenzo, Ryan Susice and Danny Johnson filling out the top 5.
The Empire Super Sprints closed out their season with a 25-lap feature, and Mark Smith picked up the $3,000 victory. The Sunbury, Pa., driver took the lead from Mike Stelter on the fifth lap and was never seriously challenged.
Chuck Hebing was second with Mahaney, Scott Kreutter and Robbie Stillwagon making up the rest of top five. There were 31 ESS sprint cars on hand.
